title: About
text: My name is Kaitlyn Schmeling and I am a senior at UNL, studying Sports Media and Mass Communications. Right now I am working for the Huskers Athletic Fund on their development team. I am planning on continuing to work here post graduation in May, working alongside their Premium Seating and Hospitality Director and Donor Relations Director! I love working in sports, especially the volleyball games and men’s basketball!

title: 2024 Big Ten Volleyball Season Results
text:
With almost a near perfect season the Husker Volleyball team had their eyes set on making it to the National Championship for the 2024 season. Sadly, the Nebraska Volleyball team did not have the outcome that they were hoping for, falling short in the Final Four. First, let’s dive into looking at the kills per set from other teams in the Big Ten.


Code
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

Code
#|\\ message: false
#|\\ warning: false 
library(readr)

data <- read.csv("2024_big_ten_vball.csv")

ggplot(data, aes(x=Institution, y=Kills)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(title="Kills Per Set Distribution", x="Institutions", y="Kills",
       subtitle ="Nebraska's biggest competition came down to Penn State.",
       caption = "Source: Big Ten Data | By: Kaitlyn Schmeling") +
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))









From this box plot, you can see that Penn State has climbed to the top of kills per set, with Nebraska following closely behind. Nebraska had lost to Penn State in the Final Four, that caused their season to end.
